{"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/DefaultBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/WinUIBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Gtk3Backend"]}],"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"SwiftCrossUI"}],"title":"GtkBackend","roleHeading":"Article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"While Gtk isn’t the preferred UI framework on every Linux distro, it’s the closest thing SwiftCrossUI has to a native Linux backend for now. The Qt backend may be brought back to life at some point to cover the rest of Linux distros.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For targetting older pre Gtk 4 Linux distros, see the secondary "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Gtk3Backend"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This backend supports Linux, macOS, and Windows, but its support for macOS has a few known issues worse due to underlying Gtk issues (and its support for Windows isn’t well tested)."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"System dependencies","anchor":"System-dependencies","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before you can use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"},{"text":" you must install the required system dependencies for your platform. Here are installation instructions tailored to each supported platform;","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Linux","anchor":"Linux","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# Debian-based distros","sudo apt install libgtk-4-dev clang","","# Fedora-based distros","sudo dnf install gtk4-devel clang"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 1: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"installing the required dependencies on Debian-based and Fedora-based Linux distros","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you run into errors related to not finding ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gtk\/gtk.h"},{"text":" when trying to build a swift-cross-ui project, try restarting your computer. This has worked in some cases (although there may be a more elegant solution).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are on a non-Debian non-Fedora distro and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" requirements end up differing significantly from the requirements stated above, please open a GitHub issue or PR so that we can improve the documentation."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"macOS","anchor":"macOS","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","code":["brew install pkg-config gtk4"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 2: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"installing the required dependencies using Homebrew","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you don’t have Homebrew, installation instructions can be found at ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/brew.sh","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It should also be possible to use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gtk4"},{"type":"text","text":" installed via MacPorts, but I have not tested that."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you run into errors related to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"libffi"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FFI"},{"type":"text","text":" when trying to build a swift-cross-ui project with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"},{"type":"text","text":", which can occur when certain older versions of the Xcode Command Line Tools are installed, try running the following command to patch libffi:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["sed -i '' 's\/-I..includedir.\/\/g' $(brew --prefix)\/Library\/Homebrew\/os\/mac\/pkgconfig\/*\/libffi.pc"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 3: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"fixing the ","type":"text"},{"code":"libffi","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" issue that some people face","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Windows","anchor":"Windows","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows things are a bit complicated (as usual), so we only support installation via "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/microsoft\/vcpkg"},{"type":"text","text":". First, install vcpkg;"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["git clone https:\/\/github.com\/microsoft\/vcpkg C:\\vcpkg","C:\\vcpkg\\bootstrap-vcpkg.bat"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 4: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"install vcpkg (requires git cli)","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"aside","style":"warning","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It’s important to install vcpkg at the root of a drive due to limitations of the Gtk build system.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Warning"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After installation, make the following changes to your environment variables:"}]}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set the "},{"code":"PKG_CONFIG_PATH","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable to "},{"code":"C:\\vcpkg\\installed\\x64-windows\\lib\\pkgconfig","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This is only required for building."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add ","type":"text"},{"code":"C:\\vcpkg\\installed\\x64-windows\\bin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to your ","type":"text"},{"code":"Path","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable. This is only required for running.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With vcpkg installed, you have two options for Gtk installation; global installation, and project-local installation","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Global Gtk 4 installation (recommended)","anchor":"Global-Gtk-4-installation-recommended","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that the command depends on your machine’s architecture; choose between Figure 5 and Figure 6 accordingly."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Installation can take 45+ minutes depending on your machine."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install gtk --triplet x64-windows"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 5: ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"install Gtk 4 globally on x64 Windows"}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install gtk --triplet arm64-windows"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 6: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"install Gtk 4 globally on arm64 Windows"}]}]},{"type":"aside","style":"warning","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Run the chosen command at the root of your drive to ensure that vcpkg doesn’t run in manifest mode."}]}],"name":"Warning"},{"type":"heading","text":"Project-local Gtk 4 installation (more unreliable)","anchor":"Project-local-Gtk-4-installation-more-unreliable","level":4},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the absolute path to your project contains spaces, it is possible 